            "body": "Sorry, I misunderstood what you were trying to say. In lua you can set an error handler with `xpcall` that can get the stack trace.\r\n```lua\r\nxpcall(function()\r\n  error('error message')\r\nend, function(err)\r\n  print(debug.traceback(err))\r\nend)\r\n```\r\nFor error messages without a stacktrace you can use `nvim_err_writeln`.",
